deck: Learn what brings eight fighters from different corners of the world to a bizarre metropolis known as Virtua City, the center of a brooding and dark secret of world domination. Are the Virtua Fighters the saviors against a secret society's evil plans, or are they mere pawns in their malicious schemes?
name: Virtua Fighter

description: The titanic team-up of the year continues! With the time-tossed Cap and Namor held by Tony Stark and his Mighty Avengers, Toro and Bucky are off-the-grid under the protective wing of the New Avengers… while the Torch finds himself in the presence of the most powerful threat to the Marvel Universe, whose identity is revealed in this issue!
name: Man on Fire

description: It’s a showdown in the Motor City as X-Factor goes toe-to-toe with the mysterious Karma organization. And when it seems the team is at its darkest moment, Madrox loses all control. Meanwhile, Val Cooper and her government forces claim to be working in X-Factor’s best interest. But are they really?
A battle 55 years in the making... Against the power of Baron Zemo!
name: V For Victory... Again!

description: The return of Flag-Smasher!
name: Full Court Press

description: The battle that began in CAPTAIN AMERICA #35 continues here! Who is Protocide? Why was he the first to take the famed Super-Soldier Serum? Why did he never become Captain America? Join us to see how things might have turned out very differently for the shield-slinger in a story that, like our other 2000 Annuals, ties directly into the ongoing series!
name: Who is... Protocide?!

description:
Overview

Does the new U.S. President believe that Captain America is expendable? This decades-spanning tale starts in the White House, then rockets back to the '40s to reveal an untold secret! What will the Living Legend do when he learns that his own government held plans to deny his very existence during W.W.II? Does the new Administration still believe that Cap is expendable? And what are the mysterious ties that link the star-spangled Avenger to our current President? Find out in this all-new Annual!
name: Denial

description:
Dynamite continues to present the most the most savage stories that comic creators have ever told! Each issue of the bi-monthly Savage Tales features a rotating cast of characters and creators featuring the savage and brutal worlds of Red Sonja and more!

This month we kick off a brand-new red Sonja two-parter by Mike Lieb and Diego Bernard! Also, look for the continuing stories of Valaka (Part 2) by Doug Murray and Lui Antonio, part 1 of a brand new Hercules story by Doug Murray and Fabiano Neves and the finale of the second arc in the Dynamite saga of Atlantis by Leah Moore, John Reppion and Pablo Marcos!
name: Age Before Beauty Part One / Battle for Atlantis Act II Part III: Master of Puppets / The Choice of Hercules Part One / Valaka Part Two

description:
Know this, reader of these texts -- Red Sonja has perished! Fallen in battle with the vile sorcerer Kulan Gath, Sonja gave her life to save all of Hyboria.

For a time, the red-maned warrior did journey through Hades at the side of the boatsman Charon. Here, she did learn the truth of her own creation at the hands of the false Goddess Scathach.

Twenty winters have passed since last Sonja walked the land. However, now that she has returned, her new incarnation self has yet to learn the truth of her existence, or the reason for her miraculous rebirth...

Our opening arc of this exciting and dangerous new direction for Red Sonja concluded last issue and now the confused She-Devil and Osin struggle to move forward and continue the quest for the Blood Dynasty!
name: Red Sonja and the Pirates, Part 5

description:
The first of three story arcs written by three of the hottest writers in crime fiction starts here! Best-selling crime novelist Gregg Hurwitz (The Kill Clause, The Crime Writer) and Laurence Campbell (PUNISHER ANNUAL: THE HUNTED) bring you a tale of death, depravity and revenge south of the border.

Cutting a bloody swathe through the dusty Mexican desert town of Tierra Rota, Frank works his way up the food chain of a criminal empire, unaware of what waits for him at the top. An old acquaintance with a familiar -- and unforgettable -- face.
name: Girls In White Dresses, Part 4: Satan Dust

description: From the wind-scoured North they’ve come: THE HORDES OF CHAOS, ruthless warriors raised in battle and fanatically devoted to their dark gods.  On a hundred-mile front across the Northern fringes of the Empire, the defenses of man and his dwarf allies are crumbling, fear threatens to become panic, and the blood of martyrs runs ankle-deep. Here begins the hopeless quest of a ramshackle band led by a mere Greatsword Sergeant – if, of course, they don’t kill each other first…
name: Chapter I

description: Greatsword Franz Vogel and his men have endured a blood-spattered onslaught by the Hordes of Chaos and lived to tell the tale. But the primordial forest into which these survivors fled holds its own secrets, both sacred and profane. For deep in the Northern Wilderness lies the cloistered stone keep of an enigmatic Sisterhood, where Vogel and his band will find either deliverance - or eternal damnation!
name: Chapter II

description: Greatsword Franz Vogel and his men have endured a blood-spattered onslaught by the Hordes of Chaos and lived to tell the tale. But the primordial forest into which these survivors fled holds its own secrets, both sacred and profane. For deep in the northern wilderness lies the cloistered stone keep of an enigmatic sisterhood ? where Vogel and his band will find either deliverance or eternal damnation?
name: Chapter III

description: The disparate bands of men, mages and dwarfs unite to take the battle to the forces of Chaos that routed them — but they must first survive the swift, savage shadow that is stalking them, leaving man and beast butchered in its wake!
name: Chapter IV

description: In the devastating onslaught by the hordes of Chaos, the mighty armies of the Empire were shattered and routed, the survivors scattered and hunted. Now, a small contingent of men, mages and dwarfs rally a united force to assault the armies of Chaos in one final, great battle!
name: Chapter V

description:
A plague derived from green Kryptonite threatens to wipe out everyone in Metropolis in "Plague."

  1. Cover by Ed Hannigan and Klaus Janson.
  2. "Plague" written by David Anthony Kraft, penciled by Mike Chen, inked by Pablo Marcos, colored by Carl Gafford and lettered by Ben Oda.
name: Plague

description: Variant cover - see pic below.
name: Black Mist: Blood Of Kali

description: " If you thought Mother Grimm was bad for Batman's and Robin's health, wait until you meet Cyanide! She's the flip side of Mother Grimm's 'goodness,' and she's out for blood!"--DC solicitation
name: Grimm Part 4 of 5 : Fairy Tales

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
A man named Jim Downing awoke from a long coma at the same time that Spawn blew off his own head which is the only way to kill a Hellspawn. This has created an anomaly (a patch of earth where neither Heaven nor Hell hold any power) in the alley where Spawn's corpse lies. Clown is plotting something.

Last issue, everything changed! The world of SPAWN was rocked by the most stunning moment in the series' sixteen year history. And now, the mystery deepens... Sides are chosen and secrets are revealed... Experience SPAWN's bold new direction with the all-star creative team of TODD McFARLANE, WHILCE PORTACIO and BRIAN HOLGUIN.
name: Endgame, Part 2

description: Batman: Death Mask is a four-issue Batman miniseries written and drawn by Manga creator Yoshinori Natsume. It is the second official Batman story to be published in the Manga style, after Batman: Child of Dreams.

volume.name: Marvel Treasury Special Giant Superhero Holiday Grab-Bag

description:
Sublet Violents was a one shot anthology of short illustrated stories inspired by J.M. Linsner and his previous anthology series Cry for Dawn. With Subtle he wanted to have less dark/horror base stories and more action/drama based stories.  
  
 This volume includes the following stories:
  

  •  Rhyder  
  •  Ahryssia 1- Out Of The Black 
  •  The New Order    
  •  Tim Conrad. Odd Man Out  
  •  Introduction To Violents
name: Subtle Violents
Protector of Earth?

description:
Peter Parkers luckiest day shatters thanks to the Shocker. Spider-Man also learns of a surprising family line.

Spider-Man can handle anything nature throws at New York City, but nature didn't cause the earthquake that trapped Ol' Webhead in a crowded subway car. Can Spidey navigate the enclosed spaces, super villains and mob mentality?
name: Unscheduled Stop Part 1

description: A surprising miniseries that may be comics' first super-powered romantic comedy! After three years of a tumultuous marriage, Edgar and Mallory Bulson have decided to throw in the towel. That was the plan anyway, until a mysterious meteor bathed the battling couple in extraterrestrial energies...energies that gave them super-powers! Will their newfound abilities be enough to make their marriage work?
name: Thunder! Lightning!

description: Snapper Carr's sanity has been rattled by a teleport with his eyes open. Now not sure what is what, he's gathering a new team of heroes to deal with the fallout of the Invasion incident. Old friends and new will join him for general buttkicking and grand theft spaceship.
name: Blasters Special

description:
This comic follows three stories about Robin, Superboy and Warrior.  
 
Robin follows a fellow suspicious classmate. Superboy is lectured for slacking off. Warrior returns to his old school to substitute in an unruly atmosphere.  
 
It is a slightly comical look at reasons to stay in school, help others, and stand up for what you believe in.

Like his law-enforcer father and grandfather before him, FBI Special Agent Dalton Morrell has a remarkable gift: he possesses the memories of his ancestors. Now joins others with gifts of their own in a common cause — saving the world from a mysterious, chillingly malevolent force — in DISAVOWED, an ongoing HOMAGE COMICS series that's a creepy, shudder-inducing excursion into the supernatural. Written by Brandon Choi (GEN13) and Michael Heisler (DV8), with atmospheric art and covers (the first four of which fit together to form a single, powerful image) by Tommy Lee Edwards (The Blair Witch Project, WILD TIMES: DEATHBLOW), DISAVOWED begins with Dalton haunted by nightmares of the distant past...nightmares revolving around a vicious murderer whose crime spree seems to have lasted for nearly a century, continuing into the present. But 's not alone in combatting the Killer with a Thousand Faces for long, as he's soon joined by other strangely-powered entities — among them a magician with true mind-over-matter powers and a Russian-born empath trained by I.O. — who have had run-ins of their own with the secret power that lurks behind this supernatural killer. Joined by a surprising fourth member, these heroes stand together against an evil that is nearly impossible to define — and even harder to defeat — struggling to foil its plans for global annihilation as the end of the Millennium approaches.
name: Devil's Haircut
Blood Memories

description: In the year 2033, the Starbridge, an elevator to Earth orbit, is humanity's greatest achievement. Sir Archer Locke, the designer of the Starbridge, has dropped out of sight after a near-fatal accident, seeking to escape his past. Now, Locke is the cyborg known as Hammerlocke and he must return to save his creation from the deadly force of the Iron Spider. Aided by an elite team of super-humans, Hammerlocke must unravel a complex plot of deceit and murder. At stake is the future of the human race.
name: Now These Her Princes

description: The JLA guest-stars as the alien-born inhabitants of Haven struggle against the villains in their midst! In the aftermath of JLA/HAVEN: ARRIVAL (solicited in last month's issue of Previews), Haven's champions, beings with a diverse range of bizarre abilities, reveal the story of their city's strange exodus from its homeworld. But how will President Luthor welcome America's best-traveled immigrants?

This Elseworlds tale sets the JLA in the Wild West where rich industrialist Maxwell Lord seeks to build the first cross-continental railway. In his way stands Paradise, a small town almost forgettable if not for its legendary sheriff, Diana Prince. The West's only lawwoman, Prince soon finds her town destroyed and sets out to stop the man-machine responsible: Lord Havoc! In her quest she enlists the help of a motley team of gunslingers: Kid Flash, the fastest gun in the West; Katar Johnson, Cheyenne shaman with a mystic wing-harness; Booster Gold, maverick gambler for hire; and Beetle, the wild-eyed inventor.

Across the lone prairie, tyrant Maxwell Lord lays tracks for the future. His dream: to build the first cos-continental railway... and nothing will stand in his way! Not even the quiet town of Paradise, home of the sherrif oft called a wonder woman, Diana Prince.

To avenge those crushed under the iron wheel's of Lord's ambition, Diana travels high and low gathering a posse of heroes for her cause including Kid Flash, the fastest gun in the West, Katar Johnson, the Hawk Shaman, John Jones, the mysterious manhunter, with Booster Gold and the Beetle- a maverick gambler and a radical inventer.

As they pick up Maxwell's trail, they're beset by mechanical men and chased by the Pinkerton, Guy Gardner. In the final show down, Felix Faust reveals Maxwell Lord's iron steam machine... a giant metal monster who breaths flames, much to the chagrin of the manhunter Jones. Nevertheless, the heroes win, discover a captured Dominator who gave Lord his technological edge, and drive off Guy for the time being.

In the epilogue, the Beetle recounts his story to Colonel Kent, veteran and journalist who spreads the tale of the Justice Riders.

Comics' first super-powered romantic comedy continues! As they begin to grasp the full extent of their mysterious, inter-dependent super-powers, the battling Bulsons are engaged in battle by a high-tech assault helicopter. Plus, a strange, alien entity begins offering the couple cousnelling on their powers and their crumbling relationship.
name: Marital Law

description: Comics' first super-powered romantic comedy continues! Nothing complicates a break-up more than super-powers that only function when you and your former beloved are in close proximity to each other...well, nothing except the arrival of villains. Lots and lots of villains. In fact, 108 armed-to- the-teeth, trained-to-kill ninjas! Plus, that pestering alien entity reveals some surprising twists that will change the Bulsons' lives forever.
name: Love, Honor, and-- Say What?

description: Most superheroes would put aside their differences in order to celebrate the final issue of their miniseries, but can Chain Lightning and Thunderball? Will Homage Comics' favorite romantic couple stay committed to fighting crime, and each other, or will this issue be the ultimate kiss-off? We're not telling (that's why we've covered the cover art with a big question mark)! Don't miss the fun-packed conclusion to comicdom's first (but definitely not last) Super-Hero Romantic Comedy!
name: Who Said The Honeymoon Was Over

description: HOMAGE COMICS's most compelling new series continues. Ever wonder what it's like to witness murder through a killer's eyes? Cassandra Caulder knows, courtesy of a blessing that is also her curse. Trained at an early age by the Russian government, skills honed by International Operations, Cassandra is the ultimate surveillance system, able to get into other people's heads and see what they see. But what happens when she inhabits the mind of Ultimate Evil, and discovers first-hand the true measure of unspeakable horror?
name: Point of View

description: HOMAGE COMICS's spellbinding new series continues. Ex-FBI agent Dalton Morrell learns more about the strangers he's thrown in with as former stage magician Rachel Rande recounts her story. It's a heart-wrenching tale that spans from her earliest years as a child she found abandoned by the side of a lonely Nebraska highway, to her discovery of the "special abilities" that allowed her to become the world's most famous — and wealthy — magician, to the horrific onstage tragedy that ended her career. Meanwhile, the forces of the Manifest Evil converge...
name: Smoke and Mirrors

description: The fourth and final member of the Disavowed is introduced. The spotlight is on Iven, an in-vitro entity genetically engineered by the Vatican to be the ultimate force of good and humanity's greatest hope in the fight against the Manifest Evil. But is Iven's power enough to stop the march of this incredible force of darkness, even with the combined talents of the motley band which comprises the Disavowed?
name: How Soon is Now?

description: The past comes back to haunt Rachel Rande as she returns to Helle House, site of a tragedy in Rachel's past that she's tried very hard to forget. Plus, former Federal Agent Dalton Morrell learns more about his ancestors' connections to the Manifest Evil, and what this dark being has planned for the new millennium.
name: Requiscat

description: The stunning finale to the eye-popping miniseries begins with the death of one of the Disavowed. But all is not as it seems when that member happens to be one of the world's most notorious magicians. In a house that traps souls — one that hungers for more victims — the group gathers to fight the ultimate force of evil. But are they too late? Mystery, magic, mayhem, and misdirection abound in the thrilling conclusion. Miss out at your own peril!
name: Abattoir
Blowout
Don't Forget Me

description: Hammerlocke, Earth's first cyborg, returns to the Starbridge and meets its elite guard of superhuman protectors. Meanwhile, Locke's daughter Amanda faces the Iron Spider, architect of the plot against the Starbridge.
name: The Stars In Their Courses

description: While Hammerlocke struggles to readjust to life in Starbridge City, Cactus Jaq tracks Tharn through the surreal realm of cyberspace. Meanwhile, Hammerlocke's kidnapped daughter Amanda learns more about the strange Antarctic cavern that is her prison.
name: The Dreams Of Gods

description: Hammerlocke is on his way to a fateful confrontation in Earth orbit with his nemesis the Iron Spider when he relives the deadly accident that cost him his humanity. Meanwhile, Cactus Jaq and Sahara Skyhawk prepare for a suicide mission to Antarctica.
name: Who Sees With Equal Eye

description: While Hammerlocke fights for his life in Earth orbit, Cactus Jaq and Sahara Skyhawk attempt to rescue Hammerlocke's kidnapped daughter. One of them will not survive!
name: What Fate Imposes

description: When Tharn's army attacks the Olympus Starbridge in full force, Hammerlocke and the Phade are the last line of defense! Plus, the traitor within the Starbridge is revealed!
name: The Purple Testament

description: With the Phade held captive, Tharn's forces storm the Olympus Starbridge, leading to a no-holds-barred battle between Hammerlocke and Tharn...while Cactus Jaq makes a startling discovery.
name: With The Enduring Dead

description: Locke and the Phade fight a final battle with the Iron Spider for the future of the Starbridge - and of Earth. But even if he wins, this may be Hammerlocke's last stand.
name: The Artifice Of Eternity

description: The all-new cyborg Hammerlocke is unveiled in this historic final issue. Plus, all conspiracies are revealed in a final confrontation between Director Rhee and Cactus Jaq.
name: The Death Of Princes

description: The JLA makes a cameo appearance as the visionary maxiseries continues! As the World's Greatest Super-Heroes attempt to bring peace to the space-born city of Haven, they learn more about Haven's own heroes: The Alliance. But is there a traitor amidst these alien champions? The secrets of the DCU's newest heroes continue to unfold!

A reporter's visit to Haven offers more insights into the crash-landing that altered the landscape of the DCU! Learn how the Havenites have been changed by their arrival, and the plans that the president and his closest advisors have for America's newest city. Plus, a cameo by Superman and the debut of Hank Velveeda!

Discover more about one of DC's newest heroines: the mysterious Nia! Once under the thrall of the cruel Anathema, Nia now ranks high amongst the Havenite heroes known as the Alliance. But what scars does she bear from Anathema's enslavement? And is she truly free of her dominance?

The brutal murder of three Havenites leaves the U.S. Government and the super-heroes of the Alliance alike searching for clues. But is the culprit an Earthly bigot, or a killer from within Haven itself? And who ? or what ? is the "Eater of Filth?"

The heroes of Haven explore the "skid road" formed by their city's arrival on Earth, hoping to find lost equipment and survivors from the crash. But the results of their search are nothing like what they expected, as they learn new and disturbing things about the natives of the world that is now home to DC's newest race of champions.

The ultra-powerful Ivas takes on the Havenite heroes of the Alliance! What is the connection between the villainous Ivas and the heroic Valadin? And how will the Alliance recover from the revelation that one of their own members is in the thrall of Anathema?

As a visit from President Luthor approaches, the heroes of Haven punish a defeated enemy, even as another, more unexpected foe is revealed! The Alliance has already found one of Anathema's pawns in a surprising place. But do they harbor another traitor in their midst?

The maxiseries reaches its shocking conclusion, setting the stage for the JLA/HAVEN: ANATHEMA one-shot! All the pieces begin to fall into place as the Alliance's seemingly heroic Valadin reveals his surprising story. What role did he have in Haven's journey to Earth? Also, learn who among the Havenites has been paving the way for the evil Anathema's arrival!

A lynch mob gathers outside of the No Hope Junction Sheriff's office demanding Bat Lash for his shooting of the sheriff in Showcase #76. Lash is rescued by his paramour Sarry Lou and heads off for greener pastures.

Along the way, he encounters the monk Brother Sebastian who tells Lash he's searching for the lost fortune of Don Sergio Aragones and hopes to use it to educate Native American children. The key to the fortune's location lies in a gold cross that has been split into three pieces, each held by a different monk. Before the two men part, Lash steals Sebastian's pocket watch and proceeds to follow the clergyman after finding the watch broken.

Hearing gunfire, Bat Lash is felled by robbers who have murdered Brother Sebastian. The next morning, Lash rides to the nearby town of Wormhole where he encounters Sebastian's niece. Soon, Lash visits the local monastery, finding it populated by peculiar monks. Returning to town, Lash is arrested on the charge of murdering Brother Sebastian but soon escapes by holding Sebastian's niece hostage. Returning to the monastery, he learns of the bandits' plot to steal the hidden fortune once the final monk arrives.

Lash intercepts the final monk, filling him in on the danger ahead. The monk rides off to summon the sheriff while Bat Lash returns to the monastery disguised as the final monk. After demanding the other piece of the cross, Lash is instead ambushed by the leader of the bandits and sells his piece of the cross to him.

Attempting to ride away in disguise, Lash encounters the sheriff and his posse accompanying Sebastian's niece to the monastery. She reveals a third piece of the cross to Lash who offers to help the sheriff capture the bandits. The treasure is soon found and our hero rides off into the sunset.
name: Bat Lash... We're A-comin' Ta Get You!

description: The Lion Force and the Council of Altarus unite to stop Empress Jain in an epic final issue. The Empress is bent on using the Voltron robots from the future to stop the original Voltron from ever being created, and even if the Lion Force succeeds, they must still find a way home to the present.

"All right, bub. Gimme my appearance schedule for October..."

"Sure, Mr. Logan! There's your regular solo title, of course. Plus, the usual line-up of team books."

"So that's just UNCANNY, ASTONISHING, NEW AVENGERS and X-FORCE. No prob."

"There's also your side projects. ORIGINS, FIRST CLASS, MANIFEST DESTINY, another FIRST CLASS..."

"Uh huh. Anythin' else?"

"Don't forget cameos! Possibly AVENGERS/INVADERS... maybe a SECRET INVASION appearance..."

"Hmph. Sounds like a light month to me. Think I got room for one more book. You got anythin' FUN?"

"Actually..."
name: A Fight At The Museum; Mini Marvels

description:
Issue tagline: "Life sucks, kids. Even when you think it doesn't."

Driven by his quest to restore Sadie's sanity, Danny tracks down the one person in the world who may be able to help - her mother. And he's called upon to make either the most noble gesture or the biggest mistake of his life. The hideous secret behind the Brown Bag Empire is revealed, and it's too absurd to take seriously. But if the revelation is true, is it any more insane than the mentally addled killer known as Tweezers?
name: Home Again, Home Again, Jiggity Jig

description:
Preparations for the final cosmic conflict continue! Meanwhile, the Weird and Starfire make a deal with the devil in order to save Rann.

Summary:
Synnar's plans to ultimate victory seems to be unstoppable. But Adam Strange and the rest of the heroes will try one last attempt to stop their extinction. Strange and Comet will head to Synnar's satellite. In the meantime, Starfire and the Weird will have to face the cruel Lady Styx in order to pact an unholy alliance. The Armageddon is near, and if Strange's ephinany is correct, few heroes will come out of this one alive.
name: On the eve of...

description: Mr. Monster creator Michael T. Gilbert spins an offbeat story of a down-on-his-luck loser who gets the chance to be Superman! How will the former Man of Steel get his body back from a guy who really likes having fame, respect and, oh yeah, super-powers?

name: A Girl And Her Ideals Are Soon Parted

description: Who will decide the shape of the future? MY NAME IS CHAOS graphically examines two astounding possibilities. Thomas Valis, an uncommon man in uncommonly trying times, has been chosen by ancient, immortal beings to be Earth's first superior human. His brother Steven, a brilliant, horribly scarred scientist, creates superhuman Mandroids using the marvels of 21st-century science. These two types of super-beings - cosmically endowed and artificially created - provide the foundation for a drama of intensities, reaching from the depths of a war-torn Earth to the sands of a newly-colonized Mars...and beyond.
name: The Song That Laid Waste To The Earth

description: Since childhood, rock musician Adam Case has heard the voices of spirits, gods and the dead. It seems not only mortals but supernatural beings are drawn to Case's music. Seeking to exploit that power is Pain, the right-hand corpse of Desire from the pages of The Sandman, who has decided that Case would make the perfect tool for his apocalyptic purposes. Written by John Ney Rieber, each issue of Mythos is illustrated by different artists.
name: Shut Heaven

description: The monsters from Wetworks unite as a force for good to save the world from demons! A thousand years have passed since the world's monsters, the Night Tribes, were brought together in a truce in order to defend the Earth against demonic invasion. A prophecy foretold a new demon lord, against whom each of the Night Tribes would send a "Chosen One." Now the time of the prophecy has come, and only the Night Tribes can save the planet. But can the Tribes put aside their hatreds of each other and work with WetWorks' Jackson Dane and Pilgrim to defeat their common enemy?
name: A Gathering of Monsters

description:
Notes:

  • 16 pages and no ads.
  • No creator data was provided.
  • Inside front cover a word from Nolan Ryan.
  • "Tony's Teaser" Inside back cover contains a word puzzle.
  • Back cover allows you to create a Nolan Ryan stand up picture.
name: The Winning Pitch!

description:
Overview:
 
Prince returns in an all-new one-shot adventure as the pop sensation and his band, the New Power Generation, journey to the Middle East to aid a princess in her quest for the lost Three Chains of Gold. The Chains are potent magical artifacts that, when combined, give the possessor control of an empire.
name: Three Chains Of Gold

volume.name: Prince and the New Power Generation: Three Chains of Gold

description:
Overview:
 
It's a fantasy epic in which Prince is locked in mortal combat with a man from his past who can turn music into the greatest destructive force the world has ever seen.
name: Alter Ego

description:
During the times of King Arthur, a evil knight called Ruber tries to kill King Arthur but Sir Lionel (a loyal knight) saves him and ends up being murdered by Ruber. A few years later Lionel's brave daughter Kayley, who dreams to be an Knight like him embarks on an adventure when Ruber kidnaps her mother (Julianna) and Excalibur disapears
Along the way, she meets up with a young blind hermit, a goofy two headed dragon and a mysterious silver winged falcon and together and tries to find the sword and warn King Arthur.
name: Quest For Camelot

description: Your parents are dead. Your little sister thinks she's Lobo. Child Protective Services wants to talk to you. Three of your best friends have superpowers they hate. And you've just inherited a Winnebago. What do you do? Road trip! THE TITANS' Devin Grayson joins the BATMAN: HARLEY QUINN art team of Yvel Guichet and Aaron Sowd to introduce the Weinbergs in RELATIVE HEROES, a 6-issue miniseries filled with enough action, humor and superhuman drama to attract both diehard super-hero buffs and readers newer to comics. After the death of their parents, the Weinbergs decide they've "had an origin," and pile into the late Mr. Weinberg's Winnebago to traverse the DCU in search of Superman, their grail of steel. Led by the only powerless sibling, Joel (a.k.a. Houston), a teenager who learned everything he knows about being a team leader from comic books, the Weinbergs are a family whose powers reflect their personalities: 11-year-old Aviva (Temper), whose electric powers make her tantrums deadlier than most; adopted brothers Tyson (Blindside), an African American, treated like an invisible man, who possesses the power to disappear, and Cameron (Omni), so outgoing he's unaware that he mimics the powers of the super-beings near him. They're joined on their road trip by Temper's baby-sitter, Damara (Allure), who is well liked by everyone...especially boys. But is she loved for who she is or because of her "charm spell?" Their adventures pit them against the police, the Department of Extranormal Operations, Child Protective Services, super-villains, and test their own limitations as a family and as human beings. The very powers they possess bring them into direct confrontation with the worst aspects of adolescence, the capacity to inflict harm, a heightened sense of social invisibility, uncontrollable, uncomfortable feelings around members of the opposite sex, and the heady feeling that you can do anything at all, as long as your friends are there with you.
name: Fate and Other Accidents

description:
Plot Summary

After being freed from a compound in New Mexico, four teenagers find themselves on the run from the government. Led by Arnold Burnsteel, their driver and self-appointed manager, the gang form a rock band as a way to camouflage themselves on the road.
name: Blitzkreig Bop

description: Wally West recounts the tale of the only time he saw Barry Allen show a hint of fear in "Burning Secrets." Script by Mark Waid, art by Jim Aparo & Bill Sienkiewicz. Also: Jesse Quick in "Like Straws in a Hurricane" by Bill Messner-Loebs, Kenny Martinez & Anibal Rodriguez; Max Mercury in "Child's Play" by Brian Augustyn, Dusty Abell & Drew Geraci; Jay Garrick in "A Stranger With My Face" by John Byrne; 'Mystery Flash' in "The Sacrifice" by Mark Waid, Brian Augustyn, William Rosado & Sal Buscema. 2-page pin-up by Phil Jimenez.

Tainted tells the story of George Palmer, a seemingly average white-collar worker with a seemingly average life. When he decides to rent out his childhood home, in an attempt to find closure over the deaths of his sister and parents, he begins to notice a strange smell pervading the property.

George struggles to adjust to his new life, and new tenants - one a young man with a heroin addiction, the other a nurse with a sideline in drug dealing. As events spiral out of his control, George is forced to confront a dark and shameful past, and is pushed to the brink of insanity.
